To Keep the track on Api Usage!

= If you're using ASP.NET Core

You can also monitor runtime metrics using:

DOTNET-COUNTERS MONITOR --PROCESS-ID <PID>

This shows:

Requests/sec
CPU usage
Garbage Collection activity
Thread Pool utilization
Memory usage

To download it:

dotnet tool install --global dotnet-counters

to find the process id :

dotnet-counters ps

u will get something like this :
Ex:
 34876  DNSFilter Agent                           [Elevated process - cannot determine path]
 16776  Dell.CoreServices.Client                  [Elevated process - cannot determine path]
 10860  Dell.Digital.Delivery.Service.SubAgent    [Elevated process - cannot determine path]
 
 then Run the commnd:
 Dotnet-counters monitor --process-id 34876
 
 it will give u the usage details
 
 
 